@okram did you understand the nature of the comment @dalaro made about #466 ? 

All tests pass with `docker/build.sh -t -n -i`

VOTE +1

Oh, now I see what you're saying. Yes, this would be the right way to go. The current `PropertyMapStep` implementation is pretty weird.

``` java
protected Map<String, E> map(...) {
    final Map<Object, Object> map = new HashMap<>();
    ...
    return (Map) map;
}
```

The lambda traversal will throw a regular NoSuchElementException as it is unparented.
However, won't this will only happen once? The exception will bubble up and out of the top level traversal?

If they did this

```
g.V().blah().map{ x -> 
  try {
    __.inject(x).will().not().have().anything().next()
    return "foo";
  }
  catch(NoSuchElementException e) {
    return "bar";
  }
}
```

instead of

```
g.V().blah().map{ x -> 
  if(__.inject(x).will().not().have().anything().hasNext()) {
    return "foo";
  }
  else {
    return "bar";
  }
}
```

Then they would have a problem.
